BugFix: set_gpu_minors expected a list of strings but start was passing a lsit of int

BugFix: added an if to prevent Status from accesing provider.process.pid if provider.process is not initialized
BugFix: added the missing line that starts the provider
BugFix: added reload to methods that access container attrs BugFix: made all times in the runtime calculation offset-naive
removed timestamps from logs since its already part of the formatter

BugFix: removed interaction with the queue from write_template methods of Containers and ContainerList. This could cause an issue where the queue had already advanced and update() and write_template() had different information about the containers
BugFix: added default values to write_template in Containers and ContainerList so that it won't crash on __call__
BugFix: wrapped reload in a try block so that it doesn't crash if the container does not exixt anymore
BugFix: correctly set displayed_information to an empty list in Containers and ContainerList
BugFix: gpu_stats() should not be blocking anymore
BugFix: stopped container stat streams before pickling
added method to stop gpu hardware monitor
added small wrapper for stopping container stat streams
BugFix: moved exited container check further up so it is not skipped when now new containers are enqueued
BugFix: gpus were not assigned correctly because the environment variable was already set with 'all' during container creation
BugFix: get_gpu_infos was comparing int ids against str id provided by the containers get_gpu_minors
BugFix: added a case for containers that have 'none' or 'void' in NVIDIA_VISIBLE_DEVICES
BugFix: changed Container init to accept a docker image. docker container is now build at Container.start(). Once a container is created there appears to be no way of changing the GPU isolation
BugFix: queue was crashing if the container object was not created yet due to the way created_at worked. fixed it
cosmetic changes
BugFix: history is now loaded properly
BugFix: redraw() now correctly checks if the self.func is an instance DisplayFunction or a subclass of it in SubWindow and SunWindowAndPad
undid last bugfix, it didnt work
BugFix: fixed disappearing borders after tabbing out
BugFix: wrapped update in Containers in a try block to avoid some timing issues
BugFix: replaced global variables with instance attributes in spit_screen
removed debug logs
